# [Goal Description]

The goal is to cleanly swap the terminology in the app to match standard PMS (Property Management System) language:
- What we currently call "rooms" (e.g. Deluxe King) will be renamed to **"room types"** (collection: `room_types`).
- What we currently call "room inventory" (e.g. 101, 102) will be renamed to **"rooms"** (collection: `rooms`).
- We will fully link these two collections.
- We will completely redesign the Bookings Calendar into a **Timeline / Gantt Chart view**, which is the industry standard for managing hotel bookings.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database & API Refactoring
- **Rename `/api/rooms` to `/api/room-types`**:
  - Update all DB queries inside to use the `room_types` collection.
- **Rename `/api/room-inventory` to `/api/rooms`**:
  - Update all DB queries inside to use the `rooms` collection.
  - Establish a solid connection: when fetching individual rooms, we can optionally `aggregate` or `join` to the `room_types` collection, though `roomTypeId` is already present.
- **Database Seeding ([/api/seed/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/Laksh/hotel-admin/app/api/seed/route.ts))**:
  - Change all references of `rooms` -> `room_types`.
  - Change all references of `room_inventory` -> `rooms`.

### 2. Frontend State & Navigation Refactoring ([app/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Laksh/hotel-admin/app/page.tsx) & Types)
- **Types**: rename [Room](file:///c:/Users/Laksh/hotel-admin/app/components/types.ts#2-27) interface to [RoomType](file:///c:/Users/Laksh/hotel-admin/app/components/RoomInventory.tsx#102-106). Rename [RoomInventoryItem](file:///c:/Users/Laksh/hotel-admin/app/components/RoomInventory.tsx#7-20) to [Room](file:///c:/Users/Laksh/hotel-admin/app/components/types.ts#2-27).
- **State variables**: rename `rooms` to `roomTypes`. Rename `roomInventory` to `rooms`.
- **Navigation**:
  - Change "Room Types" ID from `rooms` to `room-types`.
  - Change "Room Inventory" ID from `room-inventory` to `rooms`.
- Update all prop passing across the app (Dashboard, Bookings, CheckIn, etc.) to use the renamed state variables.
- Rename the actual component files if necessary, or just their internal functions.

### 3. Bookings Calendar Redesign (Timeline/Gantt View)
The current month-view calendar in your screenshot is extremely hard to read for a hotel because it groups bookings by day rather than by physical room. 

**My Suggestion:** Now that we have individual physical rooms (101, 102, 201), we should build a **Timeline / Tape Chart view**.
- **Y-Axis (Left column)**: List of physical rooms, grouped by Room Type or Floor (e.g. Deluxe King - 101, 102).
- **X-Axis (Header)**: Timeline of continuous dates (e.g. Mar 1 to Mar 15).
- **Grid**: Each row represents a physical room. Bookings are horizontal colored bars that span from the Check-In date column to the Check-Out date column.
- **Benefits**:
  - You can instantly see which specific room a guest is assigned to.
  - You can clearly see 1-day gaps between bookings (which you can't see on a month view easily).
  - It aligns perfectly with your request to "connect the rooms and room_types".

### Execution Steps
1. Refactor all API routes and Database seeding.
2. Refactor TypeScript types, App state, and UI Prop passing.
3. Build the new `BookingsTimeline` component and replace the old Calendar view in the Bookings page.
